│   # School Unrest in Kenya – Data Analytics Project
│
│   ## Project Overview
│   This project analyzes school unrest in Kenya, including strikes, arson attacks, dormitory fires, and student fatalities. The goal is to identify key drivers of unrest and determine high-risk counties using data-driven analysis to support education policy and school safety interventions.
│
│   ## Objectives
│   - Identify counties most affected by school unrest
│   - Analyze key drivers such as infrastructure, overcrowding, and fire safety
│   - Build a Composite Risk Score (0–100) to rank counties
│   - Provide actionable insights for intervention strategies
│
│   ## Key Questions
│   - Which counties are most affected?
│   - What factors drive unrest?
│   - How can risk be measured and predicted?
│
│   ## Tools & Technologies
│   - Google Sheets
│   - Power BI
│   - Python (Google Colab)
│
│   ## Methodology
│   - Google Sheets: data cleaning, pivot tables, descriptive stats
│   - Power BI: dashboards, maps, drill-through analysis
│   - Python: correlation, regression, clustering, hypothesis testing
│
│   ## Key Findings
│   - Nakuru and Narok are the most affected counties
│   - Overcrowding strongly correlates with unrest
│   - Infrastructure & fire safety are major drivers
│   - Five high-risk counties identified using composite scoring
│
│   ## Recommendations
│   - Fire safety audits in high-risk schools
│   - Reduce dormitory overcrowding
│   - Improve infrastructure in under-resourced schools
│   - Targeted interventions in high-risk counties
│
│   ## How to Run
│   1. Clone repo
│   2. Install requirements
│   3. Run notebook in tier3_python/
│
│   ## Limitations
│   - County-level data only
│   - Correlation ≠ causation
│   - Some external factors not included
│
